Gautrain shut down at the start of the lockdown with other forms of transport. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gautrain will be back on track on Monday but on reduced services. Both trains and bus will be operating daily under stringent conditions, from 5.30am to 9.30am and then from 3pm to 7pm. READ: Gauteng beefs up enforcement at borders The Gautrain down at the start of the lockdown with other forms of transport. The rail service is resuming operations but with some restrictions. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.